
1. Gabon has been inhabited for over 400,000 years.
2. Forest covers nearly 90% of Gabon.
3. The equator only passes through 13 countries in the world, and Gabon is of them.
4. Nearly two decades ago Gabon committed to setting aside more than 10% of its landmass 
for a system of national parks.
5. Widely described as ‘Africa’s last Eden’, the Loango National Park is one of the country’s 
best wildlife-watching spots.
